triples.evidence: We perform the Fourier transform of our signal using the FFT function. This gives us the discrete frequency components of the signal.
Then, we plot the magnitude of the FFT against frequency, with frequency in hertz along the horizontal axis.
triples.o: magnitude of the FFT against frequency

concepts.term: fft resolution is limited by the number of samples we have
